## Section 3 вЂ” Identity & Access Management (IAM)

### 3A вЂ” Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

Current state: we have `tenant_users.role` but only `owner` is enforced. Other roles are not checked on API endpoints.

| Role | Priority | What To Build |
|---|---|---|
| **Owner** | вњ… Exists | Already used in `tenant_users.role` |
| **Admin** | рџ”ө P0 | Add role check middleware. Admin can manage users, not billing/delete |
| **Campaign Manager** | рџџҰ P1 | Can send campaigns, view analytics, manage audience |
| **Content Editor** | рџџҰ P1 | Can create templates, cannot send |
| **Viewer / Analyst** | рџџҰ P1 | Read-only on all pages |

**What to build for P0:**
- `require_role(roles: List[str])` middleware (wraps `require_active_tenant`)
- Invite users to workspace UI (`POST /auth/invite-user`)
- Team members page in settings (`/settings/team`)
- Role selector dropdown on invite

### 3B вЂ” SSO / SAML

| Feature | Priority | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SAML 2.0 / Google / Microsoft Entra | в¬› P3 | Very complex. Not needed for MVP. Enterprise-only feature |
| JIT Provisioning | в¬› P3 | Depends on SAML |

### 3C вЂ” Audit Logs

| Feature | Priority | What To Build |
|---|---|---|
| Log critical actions (send campaign, delete, invite) | рџџҰ P1 | `audit_logs` table: actor, action, target, timestamp, IP |
| View audit log in settings UI | рџџҰ P1 | `/settings/audit-log` вЂ” filterable table |
| Export audit log CSV | рџџұ P2 | Async CSV export |

### 3D вЂ” Network Security

| Feature | Priority | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| IP Allowlist for API | в¬› P3 | Nginx layer config вЂ” enterprise only |
| IP Allowlist for Login | в¬› P3 | Middleware check on auth endpoints |
| Session timeout config | рџџҰ P1 | JWT expiry as env var. UI input for custom value |

