## Section 4 вЂ” Sender Identity (SPF / DKIM / DMARC / BIMI)

**This is already listed in our Phase 7.5 as "Domain Verification page".**

| Feature | Priority | What To Build |
|---|---|---|
| Custom sending domain input | рџ”ө P0 | `tenants.sending_domain` field |
| DNS record generation (SPF, DKIM) | рџ”ө P0 | Display TXT records tenant must add to their DNS |
| DNS verification check | рџ”ө P0 | Background poll DNS, verify records exist в†’ mark domain as verified |
| DKIM key generation per-tenant | рџџҰ P1 | Generate RSA keypair per tenant, store private key securely |
| DMARC setup guide | рџ”ө P0 | Show recommended DMARC record, explain policy levels |
| Custom Return-Path | рџџҰ P1 | CNAME for bounce handling (`bounces.theirdomain.com`) |
| BIMI (logo in Gmail inbox) | рџџұ P2 | Complex prerequisite chain: DMARC p=reject в†’ VMC в†’ SVG Tiny PS |

**Architecture for Domain Verification:**
```
UI: /settings/domain
  User enters: mycompany.com
  Backend generates:
    SPF TXT record: "v=spf1 include:ourplatform.com ~all"
    DKIM TXT record: "v=DKIM1; k=rsa; p=<public_key_for_this_tenant>"
    DMARC TXT record: "v=DMARC1; p=none; rua=mailto:dmarc@platform.com"
  User adds these to their DNS registrar
  Backend polls DNS every hour в†’ when all 3 resolved в†’ domain status = "verified"
  Worker uses tenant's domain (From: name@mycompany.com) instead of shared domain
```

